Like most households, my mom‚Äôs kitchen too is stocked with honey. And i was faced with the question ‚Äù is honey good for dry skin‚Äú? So, I poured out a cup of honey and applied it on my face. And in just one application my skin felt so much softer! Now honey is part of my daily skin care regime.

Honey will naturally lock in the moisture in your skin, thereby reducing dryness and itching of the skin. With regular use, honey makes your skin radiant and supple, with no patches of dry or flaky skin. Honey also has anti-bacterial properties that will keep skin infections at bay. Here are a few tips on how to use honey for dry skin treatment in just few weeks.
<h5>Honey For Dry Skin</h5>
<h2>1. Facial Scrub:</h2>
Most face washes available in the market have honey as a major constituent. Now you can make your own facial scrub at half the price in the comfort of your home.
<ul>
 	<li>For this you‚Äôll need olive oil, fresh lemon juice, brown sugar and honey.</li>
 	<li>Whip up a moderately thick mask out of these ingredients in a bowl</li>
 	<li>Apply a thin layer on your face.</li>
 	<li>This mask will be a lot less abrasive and will slowly remove dead skin to reveal younger and brighter looking skin.</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. A Stronger Exfoliator:</h2>
If you suffer from very dry and flaky skin then you need to depend on an exfoliator that can remove dead cells gently and yet not harm your skin.
<ul>
 	<li>Combine 2 egg yolks and 2 tablespoons of honey.</li>
 	<li>Mix this well and apply the paste to your face and other dry problem areas.</li>
 	<li>Leave the mixture on for a good half hour before you rinse it off.</li>
 	<li>Warm the mixture before application to easily rub off dead cells.</li>
</ul>
<h2>3. Natural Moisturizer:</h2>
