Honey is super hydrating and does wonders to dry skin.
<ul>
 	<li>Add honey and a few tablespoons of Shea butter, whipped or melted.</li>
 	<li>This is a great moisturizer that can be applied from head to toe.</li>
 	<li>Alternatively, drop two tablespoons of honey and cocoa butter into a bowl.</li>
 	<li>To this add 2 drops of bergamot oil and one single drop of lavender oil.</li>
 	<li>Mix the ingredients well till they blend into each other.</li>
 	<li>Once the mixture is ready slowly apply it onto your face and other affected parts of the body.</li>
 	<li>If you wish to use this mixture for your entire body you may need to make larger quantities.</li>
 	<li>Keep any remaining mixture in a bowl and cover it with a lid.</li>
 	<li>The paste may solidify so simply microwave it for the next application!</li>
 	<li>Make sure you use this mixture after a bath on clean and dry skin!</li>
 	<li>Leave the mixture on for just about 20 minutes, before washing it with a mild face wash or plain water.</li>
 	<li>Honey will lock in the natural moisture in your skin leaving it feeling fresh and soft to touch.</li>
</ul>
